headline.main: THE GREENWICH-STREET TRAGEDY.; The Investigaiton Before the Coroner Concluded. The Joseph Walker.

docs.lead_paragraph: Yesterday morning Coroner HILTON resumed the investigating (postponed form Monday,) into the particulars of the Friday of last Friday night, in the JOHN B. HOLMES, of said Ward. The Passenger was brought from the Tombs to the Coroner's Office, about 11 1/2 A.M. In coming to the rooms he way supported by two officers, being in such a weak state as to be unable to walk.
